             Zhongshan Public Utilities Group Co.
said its former chairman Tan Qingzhong and former general
manager Zheng Xuling were arrested on accusations of
unauthorized release of information, according to a statement to
Shenzhenâ€™s stock exchange.  
 Former general manager Zheng has also been accused of
insider trading, according to the statement.  
 The company had earlier announced the resignation of Tan
and Zheng on July 7.  
